	Let 𝒫 be a finite classical polar space of rank d≥3 and with parameter e≥1, embedded in a projective space over _q. A set 𝒮 of generators of 𝒫 is called pseudopolar if


  (i) the number of elements of 𝒮 meeting a given generator of 𝒮 in a (d-2)-space equals d1qq^e-1;

  (ii) the number of elements of 𝒮 disjoint to a given generator of 𝒮 is nonzero;

  (iii) |𝒮|=∏_i=0^d-1(q^e+i-1+1);

  (iv) any point of 𝒫 is contained in 0 or ∏_i=0^d-2(q^e+i-1+1) elements of 𝒮.

	Let 𝒫 be a finite classical polar space of rank d≥3 and with parameter e≥1, embedded in a projective space over _q. A set 𝒮 of generators of 𝒫 is called kind if


  (i) the number of elements of 𝒮 meeting a given generator of 𝒮 in a (d-2)-space equals d1qq^e-1;

  (ii) the number of elements of 𝒮 disjoint to a given generator of 𝒮 is nonzero;

  (iii) the number of elements of 𝒮 meeting a given generator not in 𝒮 in a (d-2)-space equals q^e-1+1;

  (iv) for every point P of 𝒫 and every generator π∉𝒮 through P, either for all j=0,…,d-2 the number of generators of 𝒮 through P meeting τ in a j-space is non-zero and it equals q^e+1+1 if j=d-2, or else for all j=0,…,d-2 it is zero.

